The paper focuses on the automatic search for optimal convolutional neural network architectures, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses genetic programming as the search method, which falls under the category of evolutionary computation and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the category of computational neuroscience, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves the design of genetic operators, which falls under the category of control theory and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
